rior notice. By using the Website you agree to be bound by all current terms and conditions. You are advised to read these terms and conditions on a frequent basis.</p><p>11. You must be at least 18 years of age, or the legal age of majority in the jurisdiction where you are located, whichever is greater, to play any of the Games</p><p>12. You must not play any Game if you are located in a jurisdiction where playing a Game is prohibited by any applicable law or regulation.</p><p>13. You may not play any Game if you or a member of your household are or have ever been an employee of International Game Technology of 9295 Prototype Drive Reno, NV 89521 United States (IGAM), IGT or any of IGAM’s or IGTs subsidiaries or associated companies. For the purposes of this clause employee” includes third party contractors such as licensors, software suppliers, developers or partners and all those persons in any way affiliated with IGAM, IGT or any of IGAMs or IGTs subsidiaries or associated companies.</p><p>14. Should you wish to play a Game you will be required to apply to open a customer account with the Website Provider. The Website Provider is exclusively responsible for the opening of accounts through the Website, banking and account management.</p><p>15. In these terms and conditions reference to an account is a reference to an account with the Website Provider.</p><p>16. Subject to these terms and conditions and the terms and conditions of use of the Website, when you open an account through the Website you become entitled to play the Games.</p><p>17. When you log into your account and choose to play a Game you will navigate away from the Website Providers game server to WagerWorks game server in Guernsey.</p><p>18. To play a Game you must have sufficient funds credited to your account. You can only place a wager from your account.</p><p>19. When you choose to play a Game you will be prompted to buy in to the Game either by using a graphical slider or by entering an amount. This allows you to place a wager on the Game. When you place a wager, funds of a value equal to the amount you have specified will be transferred to WagerWorks and at the end of your gaming session your account with the Website Provider will be updated with any remaining funds.</p><p>20. Wagers are only valid if accepted by WagerWorks server. Until acceptance of the wager by WagerWorks server all information displayed relating to a Game constitutes an invitation to play only.</p><p>21. You agree that WagerWorks records shall be the final authority in determining the validity and terms of any wagers you place and the circumstances in which they were made.</p><p>22. Wager Works reserves the right, at its sole discretion, to refuse or limit any wager you place.</p><p>23. Where a wager is invalid, refused or its value limited, any sum deducted from your account with respect to that stake will be credited to your account.</p><p>24. It is your responsibility to note the payout rate or odds that apply to each Game before you place a stake. Pay out rates and odds change from time to time.</p><p>25. When you update a loss or stake limit whilst playing a Game that loss or stake limit will not be updated until you close the current gaming session and start a new one.</p><p>26. WagerWorks reserves the right, without explanation, not to allow any person to play a Game.</p><p>27. Subject to clauses 32 and 33 WagerWorks will not be given your name, address or credit card number by the Website Provider but will be given a unique identifying number that enables it to update your game results and your account balance according to your Game winnings and/or losses at the end of each gaming session.</p><p>28. WagerWorks may collect information about your computer including, where available, your IP address, operating system and browser type. This is statistical data and does not identify any individual.</p><p>29. WagerWorks uses cookies to keep track of your personal preferences whilst playing a Game. Cookies help ensure a better playing experience.</p><p>30. A cookie is stored on the hard drive of your computer. Cookies contain information that is pertinent to the game session you have initiated. You may refuse to accept cookies by activating the setting within your browser. However, if you select this setting you may find certain Games less enjoyable. Unless you have adjusted your browser setting so that it will refuse cookies, cookies will be issued to your system when you use the Website.</p><p>31. In the event that you win MegaJackpots&reg;:</p><p>32.1. the Wesbite Provider will provide WagerWorks with the following information: your name, age, town, county, state and/or country of residence together with the fact that you have won MegaJackpots&reg;; and</p><p>33.2. you will be required to supply proof of your identity, residence and age to WagerWorks.</p><p>34. When you play a MegaJackpots&reg; Game you authorise WagerWorks, in the event that you win MegaJackpots&reg;, to publicise your name, town, county, state and/or country of residence together with the fact that you have won MegaJackpots&reg;.</p><p>35. Verification of a win in a MegaJackpots&reg; Game can take up to 72 business hours. If you win MegaJackpots&reg; you only become entitled to the prize money once your win has been verified. Where a win is not verified to Wagerworks’ satisfaction that win can be annulled by WagerWorks.</p><p>36. If you win MegaJackpots&reg; you will be informed in writing when your win has been verified.</p><p>37. Except in case of a MegaJackpots&reg; win, the prize money in any Game will, as a rule and provided all these terms and conditions and all the Websites terms and conditions have been observed, be paid to you by the Website Provider.</p><p>38. In case of a MegaJackpots&reg; win WagerWorks will, provided all these terms and conditions and all the Websites terms and conditions have been observed, pay or procure the payment of the prize money to 